# See https://help.github.com/articles/ignoring-files/ for more about ignoring files.

# dependencies
/node_modules
/.pnp
.pnp.*
.yarn/*
!.yarn/patches
!.yarn/plugins
!.yarn/releases
!.yarn/versions

# testing
/coverage

# next.js
/.next/
/out/

# production
/build

# misc
.DS_Store
*.pem

# debug
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
.pnpm-debug.log*

# env files (can opt-in for committing if needed)
.env*
!.env.example

# vercel
.vercel

# typescript
*.tsbuildinfo
next-env.d.ts

# Private planning/strategy docs — never let these reach the public repo.
# Before the first push, run `git ls-files` and confirm none of these appear.
PLAN-FULL.md
PLAN-LITE.md
TODOS.md
CLAUDE.md
LEARNING.md
MEMORY.md
.claude/

# weaponx engine data (build audit trail) and git worktree scratch space —
# operational/internal, not part of the public app.
memory/
state/
benchmark/
.worktrees/

# PLAN-LITE.md and TODOS.md contain internal strategy reasoning (why specific
# Influur-adjacent features are deliberately withheld, IP-risk discussion) —
# private, same as the other planning docs, even though PLAN-LITE is the
# active build target.
#
# BUILD-EXPLAINED.md is intentionally NOT ignored — it's meant to be public
# (a plain-language walkthrough for the cover letter/repo), written carefully
# to avoid spilling PLAN-FULL.md/PLAN-LITE.md specifics. Review it before the
# first push — it must describe WHAT was built and WHY in engineering terms,
# never "why we hid X from Influur."
